00:43.210 --> 00:44.662
Bigelow.

00:46.004 --> 00:49.006
- Well, what did I do now?
- Nothing.

00:49.007 --> 00:53.553
I, uh, just thought you'd want
to know. There's trouble.

00:53.554 --> 00:56.305
I thought you said
I didn't do nothing.

00:56.306 --> 00:59.350
Oh, no, not you. I, uh...

01:01.395 --> 01:03.813
I can't tell you where I heard it,

01:03.814 --> 01:07.692
but I heard things ain't going
so good for your kinfolk...

01:07.693 --> 01:09.395
Down on Earth.

01:10.320 --> 01:12.572
There's trouble?

01:12.573 --> 01:15.074
- Is it Julie?
- Well, I don't know exactly.

01:15.075 --> 01:17.827
- Well, is it my boy?
- I told you I don't know.

01:17.828 --> 01:20.121
Well, now, ain't that just dandy?

01:20.122 --> 01:22.498
Here you take the trouble to tell
me there's trouble down there,

01:22.499 --> 01:24.917
but you don't know what
kind of trouble it is.

01:24.918 --> 01:27.336
Do me a favor, will you?

01:27.337 --> 01:31.792
Go... Bother somebody else
while I finish these...

01:32.926 --> 01:35.428
- ...stars.
- All right.

01:35.429 --> 01:39.475
I just thought you might want
to go down there, maybe help.

01:41.101 --> 01:43.019
Who, me?

01:43.020 --> 01:45.393
You gone loony or something?

01:46.857 --> 01:48.316
How?

01:48.317 --> 01:51.694
Well, everybody's got a right
to go back for one day.

01:51.695 --> 01:53.613
- They have?
- Sure.

01:53.614 --> 01:55.865
That's the only reason I told you.

01:55.866 --> 01:58.194
Hey, come here. Come here. Hey.

01:58.702 --> 02:00.786
Not that I'm interested
in going back there,

02:00.787 --> 02:04.742
but, uh, just in case I
should be, who, uh...

02:05.125 --> 02:07.251
Who gives out this permission?

02:07.252 --> 02:09.375
The star keeper.

02:09.588 --> 02:11.131
Him, huh?

02:14.217 --> 02:16.545
Well, I'll think about it.

04:08.999 --> 04:11.201
Was you wanted to see me?

04:12.711 --> 04:15.334
Yes, I was.

04:17.673 --> 04:20.216
I heard my family's in
trouble down there.

04:20.218 --> 04:23.888
Somebody tried to tell me if I
came up here and see you, why...

04:23.889 --> 04:26.308
You'd give me permission
to go back for one day.

04:26.725 --> 04:28.684
- Is that a fact?
- Yes.

04:28.685 --> 04:33.061
But as I recall, Bigelow, when you
first got here, you waived that right.

04:34.399 --> 04:36.567
- I did?
- Yep, pretty sure,

04:36.568 --> 04:38.987
but let's look at the record.

04:43.366 --> 04:47.244
Ah, here we are.
"Bigelow. Question,

04:47.245 --> 04:50.706
"'Is there anything on Earth you
left unfinished, Mr. Bigelow?

04:50.707 --> 04:54.960
"The reason I ask is you're entitled to go
back there for one day if you want to.'

04:54.961 --> 04:59.257
"Answer, 'As long as I'm here,
I might as well stay."'

05:01.009 --> 05:02.426
I said that?

05:02.427 --> 05:05.756
Why, you don't think
this book's incorrect, do you?

05:06.264 --> 05:07.681
No.

05:08.683 --> 05:11.685
Well, if that's the way it is,
that's the way it is.

05:11.686 --> 05:13.687
Wait a minute, now. Wait a minute.

05:13.688 --> 05:18.018
You know, sometimes we make
exceptions in special cases.

05:18.485 --> 05:20.232
Special cases?

05:20.737 --> 05:25.825
Oh, you mean, if a guy led a
good life, he'd deserve a break?

05:25.826 --> 05:28.869
- That kind of thing, huh?
- Mm-hmm.

05:28.870 --> 05:32.206
- I know the answer already.
- Do you, now?

05:32.207 --> 05:35.581
Now, how do you know
how we judge things up here?

05:36.253 --> 05:40.506
Eh, it'd just be wasting
your time and mine.

05:40.507 --> 05:42.550
Simmer down now,
Billy. You're forgetting.

05:42.551 --> 05:46.301
Here there is no time. This
is the beginning and the end.

05:46.763 --> 05:48.764
Why don't you tell
me about yourself?

05:48.765 --> 05:50.967
What did you do down there?

05:51.768 --> 05:53.936
What did I do down there?

05:54.396 --> 05:56.897
Oh, you mean, "What did
I do for a living?"

05:56.898 --> 05:59.942
Well, you can start
there, if you want.

05:59.943 --> 06:01.486
Well, uh...

06:02.654 --> 06:05.482
- I owned this carousel.
- You what?

06:06.908 --> 06:10.619
Look. If you know this story, what
do you want to hear it again for?

06:10.620 --> 06:15.833
Oh, I don't know the story, but I can see
through you like a pane of window glass.

06:15.834 --> 06:18.287
Now, why don't you start over?

06:19.838 --> 06:23.668
Well, I worked for this lady
who owned the carousel.

06:23.717 --> 06:24.967
Ah.

06:24.968 --> 06:27.170
But I was the main attraction.

06:31.224 --> 06:33.017
I was, wasn't I?

06:33.768 --> 06:37.313
Every night, girls
would gather around,

06:37.314 --> 06:38.898
music would be playing,

06:38.899 --> 06:42.067
the carousel would be going
round and round,

06:42.068 --> 06:45.404
the whole midway would be
packed with people,

06:45.405 --> 06:47.858
and I'd be standing up there.

07:35.580 --> 07:40.376
All right, everybody. Hurry, hurry.
Come ride on the carousel.

07:40.377 --> 07:44.713
One more glorious spin.
Hurry, hurry, hurry.

07:44.714 --> 07:48.043
Step right this way,
and come ride the...

07:49.552 --> 07:52.554
The ride starts in a few minutes,
ladies and gentlemen.

07:52.555 --> 07:56.760
Just a very few minutes. Hurry,
hurry over this way and...

08:07.070 --> 08:10.319
Do you mind?

08:12.742 --> 08:15.411
Come on, everybody.
Hurry, hurry, hurry.

08:15.412 --> 08:16.745
Ride on the carousel,

08:16.746 --> 08:19.248
the most beautiful carousel
you've ever seen.

08:19.249 --> 08:21.793
And this year it's
faster and faster.

08:22.460 --> 08:28.338
The ride of a lifetime. Fifteen minutes
for five cents is all, five little cents.

08:30.427 --> 08:32.004
Get in line.

08:37.517 --> 08:39.811
Young lady, where's your ticket?

08:40.270 --> 08:43.313
- I don't have any.
- You can buy one.

09:05.462 --> 09:06.914
Up.

09:29.069 --> 09:30.566
Julie.

09:44.167 --> 09:47.917
Julie, come on. Hurry. Come on.

09:48.421 --> 09:50.547
She's coming after
us again. Let's run.

09:50.548 --> 09:52.796
No, I ain't scared of her.

09:54.636 --> 09:59.098
Listen, you little... I've got
one more thing to tell you.

09:59.099 --> 10:02.101
If you ever so much as poke
your nose in my carousel again,

10:02.102 --> 10:05.312
I'm gonna have you thrown out,
right on your little pink bustle.

10:05.313 --> 10:08.649
You've got no call to talk to her like
that. She ain't doing you no harm.

10:08.650 --> 10:11.652
Oh, ain't she? I suppose you think I
wanna get in trouble with the police

10:11.653 --> 10:14.571
- and maybe lose my license?
- What is the woman talking about?

10:14.572 --> 10:18.033
Letting my barker fool with you.
Ain't you ashamed?

10:18.034 --> 10:21.703
- I don't let no man fool...
- He leaned against her all through the ride.

10:21.704 --> 10:24.248
He leaned against the horse,
but he didn't lay a hand on me.

10:24.249 --> 10:25.791
Oh, no, Miss Innocence.

10:25.792 --> 10:28.794
And I suppose he didn't put his
arm around your waist neither.

10:28.795 --> 10:33.006
And suppose he did. Is that a reason
to go and have a "capuleptic" fit?

10:33.007 --> 10:35.217
You mind your own
business, you hussy.

10:35.218 --> 10:37.719
Go on back to your old
carousel and leave us alone.

10:37.720 --> 10:42.182
- Yeah, leave us alone, you old...
- I don't run my business for a lot of sluts.

10:42.183 --> 10:44.810
Who you calling a slut?
Slut yourself.

10:44.811 --> 10:47.059
- Yeah, slut yourself.
- Shut up!

10:47.188 --> 10:49.148
Jabber, jabber, jabber,
jabber, jabber.

10:53.194 --> 10:55.237
What's going on anyway?

10:55.238 --> 10:58.365
Spitting and sputtering like three
lumps of corn a-poppin' on a shovel.

10:58.366 --> 11:00.701
- Mr. Bigelow, please...
- Don't yell.

11:00.702 --> 11:04.122
- I didn't yell.
- Well, don't.

11:05.248 --> 11:06.373
What's the matter?

11:06.374 --> 11:08.584
I want you to take a good
look at that girl, Billy.

11:08.585 --> 11:11.253
She ain't never to be allowed
on my carousel again.

11:11.254 --> 11:13.964
Next time she tries to
get in, if she dares,

11:13.965 --> 11:15.591
I want you to throw her out,
you understand?

11:15.592 --> 11:18.135
- Throw her out!
- All right, all right.

11:18.136 --> 11:21.138
Well, you heard what the lady said.
Go on. Go on home.

11:21.139 --> 11:23.307
- Shoo, get.
- Come on, Julie.

11:24.309 --> 11:27.978
- No, I won't.
- Would you like a nice, cool drink, Billy?

11:27.979 --> 11:29.931
- Sure.
- Mr. Bigelow.

11:31.941 --> 11:34.943
Tell me, please, honest and truly.

11:34.944 --> 11:38.990
If I come back to the carousel
again, would you throw me out?

11:42.118 --> 11:43.452
What did she do anyway?

11:43.453 --> 11:46.205
She said you put your arm
around my waist.

11:46.206 --> 11:51.627
Aha, well. There's something new.

11:51.628 --> 11:55.589
Can't put my arm around a girl without first
asking permission, is that how it is?

11:55.590 --> 11:58.839
No, I just don't want
that one around no more.

12:02.889 --> 12:05.390
You come around all you like, see.

12:05.391 --> 12:09.269
You ain't got the price, Billy
Bigelow will treat you to a ride.

12:10.355 --> 12:13.649
Big talker, ain't you, Mr. Bigelow?

12:13.650 --> 12:17.319
I suppose you think I can't
throw you out too if I want to?

12:17.320 --> 12:18.820
You're such a good barker,

12:18.821 --> 12:22.115
I can't run my business
without you, is that it?

12:22.116 --> 12:25.327
Well, just for that,
you're discharged.

12:25.328 --> 12:29.328
Your services are no longer required.
You're bounced. See?

12:29.666 --> 12:32.000
Very well, Mrs. Mullin. Very well.

12:32.001 --> 12:36.880
Well, now, you know, I could
bounce you if I felt like it.

12:36.881 --> 12:40.550
Well, you felt like it just now.
So I'm bounced, bounced.

12:40.551 --> 12:44.346
Well, now, you don't have to pick up
every word I say. I only said that I...

12:44.347 --> 12:47.391
Said that my services
were no longer required.

12:47.392 --> 12:50.971
Very good, Mrs. Mullin.
We'll let it go at that.

12:51.688 --> 12:54.064
All right, you devil.
We'll let it go at that.

12:54.065 --> 12:56.650
- Mr. Bigelow, if she said she's...
- You keep out of this.

12:56.651 --> 12:59.570
But I don't want this
to happen on account of me.

13:01.781 --> 13:04.029
- Apologize to her.
- Aha!

13:04.575 --> 13:08.620
Me apologize to her? For what?
For giving my carousel a bad name?

13:08.621 --> 13:11.449
A ba...

13:12.750 --> 13:17.046
The day you bought the carousel,
Mrs. Mullin, it got a bad name.

13:18.047 --> 13:21.126
After all I've done for
you, that's what...

13:21.384 --> 13:23.302
- Now I am through with you.
- Go on.

13:23.303 --> 13:25.012
- And it's for good, do you hear?
- Go on.

13:25.013 --> 13:26.465
Get!

13:30.059 --> 13:32.102
Through for good.

13:34.105 --> 13:37.275
And I won't take you back
like I done before.

13:37.775 --> 13:40.444
What will you do now, Mr. Bigelow?

13:40.903 --> 13:45.449
Well, first of all, I'll go get
myself a glass of beer.

13:45.450 --> 13:48.702
Whenever anything bothers me,
I always drink a glass of beer.

13:48.703 --> 13:50.912
Then you are bothered
about losing your job.

13:50.913 --> 13:55.084
No, only about how
I'm gonna pay for the beer.

13:56.377 --> 13:58.329
Will you pay for it?

14:00.089 --> 14:01.666
You?

14:03.426 --> 14:06.926
- How much money you got?
- Forty-three cents.

14:07.847 --> 14:09.424
And you?

14:10.433 --> 14:13.807
I asked you how much money you got?

14:14.270 --> 14:15.687
Oh.

14:17.065 --> 14:19.438
You don't need to cry about it.

14:19.776 --> 14:21.985
If you ain't got it,
you ain't got it.

14:21.986 --> 14:24.905
Tell her to stop crying.

14:25.531 --> 14:27.074
Carrie.

14:29.327 --> 14:31.325
Well, that's better.

14:32.038 --> 14:35.332
I'm going over to the carousel
and get my things.

14:35.333 --> 14:38.707
Hey, you know that
bench down the road?

14:39.295 --> 14:43.671
The one by the... By the water,
the last one, by the tree.

14:44.634 --> 14:46.426
I'll meet you there.

14:46.427 --> 14:49.631
And then we'll go see about
having that drink.

14:53.518 --> 14:57.518
It's all right. Keep your money.
This time, I'll pay.

14:58.940 --> 15:00.482
Julie.

15:00.483 --> 15:01.855
Huh?

15:01.984 --> 15:03.985
I've been bustin' to tell
you something lately.

15:03.986 --> 15:05.438
You have?

15:06.656 --> 15:09.324
The reason I didn't care
to tell you before was...

15:09.325 --> 15:12.828
Well, 'cause you didn't
have a fella of your own.

15:12.829 --> 15:16.533
But now that you got one,
I can tell you about mine.

15:17.708 --> 15:21.833
I'm glad you've got a fella,
Carrie. What's his name?

15:22.213 --> 15:25.674
♪ His name is Mister Snow ♪

15:25.675 --> 15:29.010
♪ And an upstanding man is he ♪

15:29.011 --> 15:32.681
♪ He comes home ev'ry night
in his round bottomed boat ♪

15:32.682 --> 15:36.261
♪ With a net full of
herring from the sea ♪

15:37.854 --> 15:41.273
♪ An almost perfect beau ♪

15:41.274 --> 15:44.651
♪ As refined as a girl could wish ♪

15:44.652 --> 15:48.280
♪ But he spends so much time
in his round bottomed boat ♪

15:48.281 --> 15:51.735
♪ That he can't seem to lose
the smell of fish! ♪

15:55.163 --> 15:58.957
♪ The fust time he kissed me
the whiff of his clothes ♪

15:58.958 --> 16:02.669
♪ Knocked me fiat on the
floor of the room ♪

16:02.670 --> 16:06.965
♪ But now that I love him
my heart's in my nose ♪

16:06.966 --> 16:12.388
♪ And fish is my
fav'rite perfume! ♪

16:13.222 --> 16:17.017
♪ Last night he spoke quite low ♪

16:17.018 --> 16:20.729
♪ And a fair spoken man is he ♪

16:20.730 --> 16:24.649
♪ And he said "Miss Pipperidge,
I'd like it fine ♪

16:24.650 --> 16:27.986
♪ "If I could be wed with a wife ♪

16:27.987 --> 16:33.200
♪ "And indeed, Miss Pipperidge
If you'll be mine ♪

16:33.201 --> 16:38.532
♪ "I'll be yours fer the
rest of my life!" ♪

16:39.081 --> 16:42.459
♪ Next moment we were promised ♪

16:42.460 --> 16:46.213
♪ And now my mind's in a maze ♪

16:46.214 --> 16:50.217
♪ Fer all it ken do
is look forward to ♪

16:50.218 --> 16:55.424
♪ That wonderful day of days ♪

16:58.142 --> 17:05.315
♪ When I marry Mister Snow ♪

17:05.316 --> 17:09.277
♪ The flowers'll be buzzin'
with the hum of bees ♪

17:09.278 --> 17:13.573
♪ The birds'll make a racket
in the church yard trees ♪

17:13.574 --> 17:20.202
♪ When I marry Mister Snow ♪

17:20.748 --> 17:27.587
♪ Then it's off to home we'll go ♪

17:27.588 --> 17:31.550
<i>♪ And both of us'll look
little dreamy-eyed ♪</i>

17:31.551 --> 17:35.512
♪ A drivin' to a cottage
by the oceanside ♪

17:35.513 --> 17:41.345
♪ Where the salty breezes blow ♪

17:42.979 --> 17:46.690
♪ He'll carry me
'cross the threshold ♪

17:46.691 --> 17:49.985
♪ And I'll be as meek as a lamb ♪

17:49.986 --> 17:54.698
♪ Then he'll set me on my feet
And I'll say, kinda sweet ♪

17:54.699 --> 17:58.870
♪ Well, Mister Snow here I am! ♪

18:01.247 --> 18:08.422
♪ Then I'll kiss him
so he'll know ♪

18:08.504 --> 18:12.841
♪ That ev'rythin'll be as
right as right ken be ♪

18:12.842 --> 18:17.137
♪ A livin' in a cottage
by the sea with me ♪

18:17.138 --> 18:24.267
♪ For I love that Mister Snow ♪

18:25.021 --> 18:29.482
♪ That young, seafarin'
bold and darin' ♪

18:29.483 --> 18:34.321
♪ Big, be-whiskered over-bearin ♪

18:34.322 --> 18:38.902
♪ Darlin' ♪

18:39.827 --> 18:47.002
♪ Mister Snow ♪ ♪

18:54.550 --> 18:57.629
- Carrie, I'm so happy for you.
- Yeah.

18:58.554 --> 19:01.428
Come on. I don't wanna be late.

19:09.565 --> 19:13.065
Carrie, this is where
he meant us to wait.

19:13.903 --> 19:16.822
- You sure?
- Yes.

19:21.702 --> 19:25.406
- It's awful quiet here, Julie.
- Yes, it is.

19:27.708 --> 19:30.331
Hardly anyone ever goes past here.

19:31.420 --> 19:34.544
Do you think the stories
about him are true?

19:35.383 --> 19:36.630
Probably.

19:43.349 --> 19:45.517
Well...

19:45.518 --> 19:47.727
What are you girls doing here?

19:47.728 --> 19:50.271
You told us to wait for you.

19:50.272 --> 19:53.271
I meant she was to wait.
You can go home.

19:54.527 --> 19:55.944
Why, Mr. Bigelow.

19:55.945 --> 19:59.319
If you think either one of us
would stay here with you alo...

20:02.159 --> 20:04.160
Oh, Mr. Bigelow, it's late.

20:04.161 --> 20:06.371
If Julie stays,
she'll lose her job.

20:06.372 --> 20:09.499
Lose your job 'cause you stay
out late? Where do you work?

20:09.500 --> 20:11.167
At Bascombe's Cotton Mill.

20:11.168 --> 20:13.795
All Bascombe's girls
have to be respectable.

20:13.796 --> 20:15.755
We all have to live in
the mill boarding house

20:15.756 --> 20:19.467
and if we're late, they lock us out and
we can't go back to work there anymore.

20:19.468 --> 20:22.220
Is that right? They bounce you
if you ain't home on time?

20:22.221 --> 20:24.719
- That's right.
- It's late, Julie.

20:25.141 --> 20:26.843
We ought to go.

20:27.935 --> 20:29.682
Are you coming?

20:31.981 --> 20:33.933
Should I go, Julie?

20:34.400 --> 20:37.149
I can't tell you
what to do, Carrie.

20:37.737 --> 20:39.314
All right.

20:40.239 --> 20:42.237
- Good-bye.
- Good-bye.

20:44.910 --> 20:46.862
Good-bye, Julie.

20:46.871 --> 20:48.698
Good-bye, Carrie.

20:49.248 --> 20:51.701
Well, now we're both out of jobs.

20:53.502 --> 20:56.046
- You had your supper?
- No.

20:59.633 --> 21:01.968
You want to eat out on the pier?

21:01.969 --> 21:03.466
No.

21:10.019 --> 21:12.979
You don't come around the
carousel very much, do you?

21:12.980 --> 21:15.940
I only seen you two or
three times before today.

21:15.941 --> 21:18.485
I've been there much
more than that.

21:18.486 --> 21:20.188
Is that right?

21:21.030 --> 21:23.073
- Did you see me?
- Yes.

21:23.699 --> 21:25.867
Did you know I was Billy Bigelow?

21:25.868 --> 21:27.911
The girls told me.

21:31.290 --> 21:33.374
- You got a sweetheart?
- No.

21:33.375 --> 21:35.668
- Now, don't lie to me.
- I haven't any.

21:35.669 --> 21:38.838
Why, you stayed here
the first time I asked you to.

21:38.839 --> 21:42.213
You wouldn't have stayed so quick
if you hadn't done it before.

21:43.552 --> 21:45.720
What did you stay for anyway?

21:46.555 --> 21:49.008
So you wouldn't be left alone.

21:49.767 --> 21:52.393
Holy smokes, you're dumb.

21:52.394 --> 21:54.979
I don't need to be alone. I can
have all the girls I want.

21:54.980 --> 21:56.397
Don't you know that?

21:56.398 --> 21:58.271
I know, Mr. Bigelow.

21:58.567 --> 22:00.815
All the girls are crazy for you.

22:01.821 --> 22:04.365
Well, that's more like it.

22:06.659 --> 22:09.077
You know what you remind me of?

22:09.078 --> 22:11.121
A girl I knew at Coney Island.

22:11.747 --> 22:13.620
Tell you how I met her.

22:13.999 --> 22:16.835
We was just putting out
the lights one night when...

22:16.836 --> 22:19.038
Is that you, Miss Jordan?

22:19.213 --> 22:21.086
Yes, Mr. Bascombe.

22:26.095 --> 22:28.763
- Whatever are you doing out at this hour?
- Well, I...

22:28.764 --> 22:31.933
You couldn't be home in time
now if you ran all the way.

22:31.934 --> 22:33.059
No, sir.

