cried in church on Sunday.

49:53.532 --> 49:57.282
Mr. Snow, you startled me!

50:01.665 --> 50:04.960
Well, this is him.

50:06.253 --> 50:08.831
- Carrie told me a lot about you.
- Oh.

50:09.840 --> 50:12.634
I told you a lot about
Julie, didn't I?

50:16.430 --> 50:18.181
Enoch's nice-lookin', ain't he?

50:18.182 --> 50:20.475
Oh, come, Carrie.

50:20.476 --> 50:22.678
Steady and reliable too.

50:24.522 --> 50:27.145
Well, ain't you gonna
wish us good luck?

50:31.445 --> 50:33.943
Course I wish you luck, Carrie.

50:35.866 --> 50:39.911
You can kiss Enoch too,
us bein' such good friends

50:39.912 --> 50:42.490
and me bein' right here
lookin' on at you.

50:50.089 --> 50:52.792
Why are you cryin', Mrs. Bigelow?

50:53.884 --> 50:56.803
It's because she has
such a good heart.

50:57.304 --> 51:00.390
We thank you for your
heartfelt sympathy.

51:00.391 --> 51:02.719
We thank you, Mrs. Bigelow.

51:06.272 --> 51:08.941
Billy! Billy.

51:15.114 --> 51:19.659
You know Carrie, and...
This is her intended, Mr. Snow.

51:19.660 --> 51:21.828
- Mr. Snow?
- Mr. Bigelow?

51:22.955 --> 51:25.123
I feel like I know you.

51:25.666 --> 51:29.086
Oh, yes. The man who
owns the herring boat.

51:31.046 --> 51:33.214
You smell it over there, Jigger?

51:33.215 --> 51:35.634
Nope. Wind's in the
wrong direction.

51:36.927 --> 51:40.847
- It's a good, honest smell!
- It's a powerful, honest smell.

51:40.848 --> 51:43.891
Carrie. You still want
me to offer him a job?

51:43.892 --> 51:44.976
What job?

51:44.977 --> 51:47.937
Mr. Snow here is thinkin'
of puttin' on another boat

51:47.938 --> 51:50.732
and I was gonna ask him to offer
you a job on it, but now I...

51:50.733 --> 51:53.026
Me? Work on a herring boat?

51:53.027 --> 51:56.195
No, thanks.

51:56.196 --> 52:00.526
Enoch, come along before you lose
your temper and do something violent.

52:03.954 --> 52:07.249
Well? Go ahead. Say it.

52:08.334 --> 52:11.002
I insulted your friends,
stayed out all night.

52:11.003 --> 52:14.172
I ain't workin'. I'm livin'
off your cousin Nettie.

52:14.173 --> 52:18.051
- I didn't say anything.
- No, but it was on the tip of your tongue.

52:18.052 --> 52:21.179
I was only gonna ask if... If you
wanted to go to the clambake.

52:21.180 --> 52:25.016
It's a good idea, Billy. You've been
actin' kind of nervous and edgy.

52:25.017 --> 52:27.477
Who knows? Maybe you
might find the treasure.

52:27.478 --> 52:29.976
No! Ain't goin' to no clambake.

52:34.026 --> 52:37.570
Well, you got anything else to say?

52:37.571 --> 52:39.530
Like what, Billy?

52:39.531 --> 52:42.530
Well, like whether
I'm hungry or not.

52:43.077 --> 52:47.205
I didn't have to ask that, Billy.
I knowed you was hungry.

52:47.206 --> 52:50.535
You go and sit down,
and I'll bring you your dinner.

52:56.590 --> 52:58.591
Do you wanna see somebody?

52:58.592 --> 53:02.387
Yeah, Billy.

53:02.388 --> 53:05.098
- That is, if he's home yet.
- He's home.

53:05.099 --> 53:07.558
Would it be asking too much
to know where he is?

53:07.559 --> 53:11.434
My husband is around the other
side, waitin' for his dinner.

53:11.897 --> 53:13.474
Thanks.

53:21.448 --> 53:23.321
Hello, Billy.

53:25.452 --> 53:26.953
Well, what'd you come for?

53:26.954 --> 53:30.456
Well, I see you're still hangin'
around your jailbird friend.

53:30.457 --> 53:32.458
What's it to you who
I hang around with?

53:32.459 --> 53:36.129
One thing I can't abide is
a common type woman.

53:36.130 --> 53:40.800
Everybody that gets mixed up with him
finishes up in the jailhouse or the grave.

53:40.801 --> 53:42.548
Common woman.

53:43.345 --> 53:47.891
Put on a new coat of paint. You're
startin' to peel, old pleasure boat.

53:50.602 --> 53:53.681
Well. What are you doin' here?

53:54.148 --> 53:56.225
You got a new barker, ain't you?

53:56.984 --> 53:59.360
Why don't you stay home
and sleep at night?

53:59.361 --> 54:00.570
- You look awful.
- Ah.

54:00.571 --> 54:03.156
Here, come on. Put your hair
back off your forehead.

54:03.157 --> 54:05.280
Oh, leave my hair be.

54:06.827 --> 54:09.662
I, uh, hear you been beatin' her.

54:09.663 --> 54:11.414
Now if you're sick of her,
why don't you leave her?

54:11.415 --> 54:14.333
- There's no use beatin' the poor thing.
- Who beat her?

54:14.334 --> 54:17.128
What's all this darn fool talk
about a beatin'? I hit her once.

54:17.129 --> 54:18.212
Oh.

54:18.213 --> 54:20.506
Now the whole town is talkin'...

54:20.507 --> 54:22.633
Next one I hear say "beat,"
I'm gonna smash...

54:22.634 --> 54:26.637
All right. All right, all right, all right.
All right. I take it back.

54:26.638 --> 54:29.515
Look, I don't wanna
get mixed up in this.

54:29.516 --> 54:32.515
"Beat her." As if I'd beat her.

54:33.645 --> 54:35.897
What's the odds one
way or the other?

54:35.898 --> 54:40.444
Why don't you look at the thing straight?
You're sick of bein' married.

54:40.861 --> 54:43.529
Carousel ain't crowded
without me, is it?

54:43.530 --> 54:47.074
Oh, Billy. You see? You belong
out there and you know it.

54:47.075 --> 54:49.410
You wasn't cut out
for a respectable, married man.

54:49.411 --> 54:52.740
You're the... You're...
You're the artist type.

54:53.040 --> 54:55.368
You belong among artists.

54:57.544 --> 54:59.246
Tell you what, Billy.

54:59.797 --> 55:01.840
You come back...

55:02.591 --> 55:06.671
And I'll give you that ruby
ring my husband left me.

55:07.429 --> 55:09.347
I don't know. I...

55:11.058 --> 55:12.760
Yeah.

55:13.727 --> 55:15.895
I might go back.

55:15.896 --> 55:19.398
Yeah. Yeah, I could still
live here with Julie, and...

55:19.399 --> 55:22.026
- Holy Moses!
- Well, what's wrong?

55:22.027 --> 55:24.111
Well, can you imagine?
The girls would love that,

55:24.112 --> 55:26.405
a barker who runs home
to his wife every night.

55:26.406 --> 55:29.575
Why, people would
laugh theirselves sick.

55:29.576 --> 55:32.450
Well, I... I know I would.

55:32.579 --> 55:35.202
Yeah. I can hear you laughin'.

55:35.958 --> 55:38.456
Don't be so stuck on yourself.

55:39.169 --> 55:42.122
- You want anything?
- Brought you your dinner.

55:50.931 --> 55:53.725
Billy? I...

55:54.309 --> 55:56.682
I got somethin' to tell you.

55:57.271 --> 55:58.973
All right.

55:59.314 --> 56:01.399
I've... Been wantin' to tell you.

56:01.400 --> 56:04.652
- In fact, I was goin' to yesterday...
- Go ahead.

56:04.653 --> 56:07.823
I can't. We gotta be alone.

56:08.615 --> 56:10.992
Can't you see I'm busy here?
I'm talkin' business.

56:10.993 --> 56:13.786
- It'll only take a minute.
- Get out of here.

56:13.787 --> 56:16.372
- I tell you. It'll only take a minute.
- Will you get out of here?

56:16.373 --> 56:18.332
- No!
- What did you say?

56:18.333 --> 56:21.707
Ah, let her alone. She's
got somethin' to tell you.

56:22.212 --> 56:26.042
And you... You've got
somethin' to tell her.

56:26.383 --> 56:28.585
I'll be back in a minute.

56:32.681 --> 56:35.933
- Well?
- Don't look at me like that.

56:35.934 --> 56:38.102
I ain't afraid of you.
I ain't afraid of anyone.

56:39.688 --> 56:43.062
Go ahead and tell me
what it is. Make it quick.

56:44.276 --> 56:47.855
Well, I... I can't
tell you so quick.

56:51.158 --> 56:53.702
Why don't you drink your coffee?

56:55.162 --> 56:57.246
Is that what you come to tell me?

56:57.247 --> 57:01.202
No, but... But by the time you
drink it, I'll have told you.

57:05.005 --> 57:06.832
Well?

57:08.467 --> 57:10.465
Well...

57:10.844 --> 57:13.804
Yesterday my head ached,
and you asked me if...

57:13.805 --> 57:15.222
Yes?

57:17.142 --> 57:19.970
Well, you see, that's what it is.

57:21.188 --> 57:23.390
I'm gonna have a baby.

57:30.030 --> 57:32.490
Julie. Julie!

57:32.491 --> 57:34.910
You ain't mad, Billy, are you?

57:35.369 --> 57:37.828
Should you be walkin'
up them stairs?

57:37.829 --> 57:40.790
- Sure, Billy.
- Here. Let me help you.

57:40.791 --> 57:45.588
I'm all right. I'm fine,
just as long as you ain't mad.

58:05.399 --> 58:08.901
♪ Dee-dah-dah-dah
Dah-dah-dah-dah-dee ♪

58:08.902 --> 58:11.362
♪ Round in circles ♪

58:11.363 --> 58:14.949
Here. You'll be wantin' an
advance on your salary.

58:14.950 --> 58:18.575
That's only fair. Now, you been
out of work a long time.

58:18.912 --> 58:20.955
Go home, Mrs. Mullin.

58:21.415 --> 58:22.915
Well, what's the matter with you?

58:22.916 --> 58:26.210
Go on back to your carousel.
Go on. Go on!

58:26.211 --> 58:30.666
- You mean you ain't comin' back with me?
- Good-bye, Mrs. Mullin.

58:31.258 --> 58:34.635
What did she tell you?
Some lies about me, I'll bet.

58:34.636 --> 58:35.928
- No.
- I...

58:35.929 --> 58:37.927
Nothin' about you.

58:39.433 --> 58:42.557
It was about me and Julie and...

58:43.895 --> 58:46.598
As a matter of fact, Mrs. Mullin...

58:48.275 --> 58:50.352
I'm gonna be a father.

58:51.778 --> 58:55.573
You? You, a father?

58:59.077 --> 59:01.245
Good-bye, Mrs. Mullin.

59:14.259 --> 59:16.093
- Hey, Jigger.
- Ah.

59:16.094 --> 59:19.594
Jigger! Julie's gonna have a baby.

59:20.307 --> 59:22.259
Well, what about it?

59:26.146 --> 59:27.689
Nothin'.

59:31.443 --> 59:33.691
My mother had a baby once.

59:42.954 --> 59:46.999
♪ I wonder what he'll
think of me! ♪

59:47.000 --> 59:51.170
♪ I guess he'll call
me "The Old Man!" ♪

59:51.171 --> 59:56.467
♪ I guess he'll think I can lick
Ev'ry other feller's father ♪

59:56.468 --> 01:00:01.219
♪ Well, I can! ♪

